No, the rogue would be sitting on his ass back at the camp I am pulling to, along with every other class.  When the mobs magically turn up one by one, the rogue would slip on auto attack and every 6 secs press the backstab macro that does auto evade while sipping his campari and requesting attention from his lady friend (hunny you made me miss backstab).<br>
<br>
&quot;Any time FD saved you, a rogue would have died anyway.&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, no, again, if the rogue ever pulls he wouldn't even be attempting to split those four mobs so that the group could get more exp.<br>
<br>
And again, the rogue would never find himself in the situation of having to tank those four mobs for the duration of FD refresh.<br>
<br>
The rogue would never discover the joys of a successful FD being broken due to...<br>
<br>
A mob chain casting until oom<br>
Two mobs chain casting until oom<br>
A well meaning cleric casting a heal while you wait for FD refresh while tanking the aformentioned mobs<br>
<br>
No, the rogue would just keep on running, shouting train to zone (using a macro of course), while thinking &quot;son of a bitch I gotta use both hands for this and I can't reach my campari&quot;.  At least the rogue gets his cherry.<br>
